Reasoning: The paper discusses the development and use of computer algebra tools for simplifying integrals and sums in the context of QCD calculations. This falls under the category of symbolic computation (cs.SC) and symbolic algebraic manipulation (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of numerical methods (cs.NA) and linear optimization (cs.LO) in the context of QCD calculations. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these tools in the context of coupled systems of linear differential equations, which falls under the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
